pressRelease.title: Wavefront And BCNET Provide Wireless Start-ups With High-bandwidth Connections To B.C. Researchers Improving Their Productivity
pressRelease.lead: Wavefront, the national commercialization centre supporting the growth of Canada's wireless companies has partnered with BCNET, a shared IT services organization dedicated to higher education and research in British Columbia, enabling technology collaboration between industry and academia to accelerate the commercialization of wireless innovation.
pressRelease.body:
Wavefront, the national commercialization centre supporting the growth of Canada's wireless companies has partnered with BCNET, a shared IT services organization dedicated to higher education and research in British Columbia, enabling technology collaboration between industry and academia to accelerate the commercialization of wireless innovation.

FusionPipe, a resident in Wavefront's accelerator program, uses BCNET's high-speed research network for testing and validating their software and setting up a hybrid cloud. They required an advanced network-testing environment to undertake and endorse their research and collaborate with researchers at SFU. Their core product, ThoriumCloud, delivers virtual desktops and secure Intranet access to tablets and smartphones.

"Through Wavefront's access to BCNET's advanced research network we were able to collaborate with researchers at SFU and quickly move from testing to prototyping," says Peter Luong, Fusion Pipe's CEO. "The high-speed network provides a direct link to transmit large amounts of data to SFU Burnaby where researchers were developing and testing cloud-based disaster recovery solutions using our technology. We're in the early days of our collaboration project with SFU that is building on the advancements of cloud computing and network virtualization. This project will put us at the centre of the future of cloud-computing - a pretty cool place to be."

The cooperation between BCNET and Wavefront is accelerating the commercialization of innovation by bridging low-cost networks between research and industry. Wavefront connects to BCNET's high-speed, high-capacity network through its Vancouver Transit Exchange, a network services exchange. The Exchange is a network neutral marketplace that directly interconnects Wavefront through a central router to over 35 research universities and institutes in Vancouver.

Linking to BCNET's Exchange enables wireless start-up organizations at Wavefront with a competitive advantage by providing unlimited bandwidth for transmitting data freely and efficiently with Vancouver's research universities and institutes by bypassing commercial network service providers.

"BCNET can help to foster innovation by enabling low-cost network peering connections between researchers and small and medium sized private enterprises through our Transit Exchanges located in British Columbia," says Michael Hrybyk, president and CEO, BCNET. "Our Exchange offers leading-edge technology that is designed to optimize data traffic for our higher education members, as well as foster community and economic development."

Wavefront received funding through CANARIE's DAIR program, the Digital Accelerator for Research and Innovation, to provision a direct fibre optic network connection between Wavefront's facilities and the BCNET Transit Exchange located at Harbour Centre in Vancouver. The Exchange reduces network costs through peering connections and provides low-cost access to nine commercial Internet service providers.

"Wavefront and BCNET's partnership provides a robust cloud-based development environment for FusionPipe's technology, speeding up their commercialization - which is what we're here to do," said Alan Swain, VP Technology and Operations at Wavefront.

About BCNET

BCNET is a not-for-profit, shared IT services organization that collaborates with its higher education members to explore and evaluate leading-edge information technology services to accelerate research, collaboration, learning and innovation. BCNET's high-capacity, advanced fibre optic network infrastructure provides a common and powerful platform to deliver services to support research and the strategic objectives of higher education institutions.

About Wavefront

Wavefront accelerates the growth and commercialization of wireless companies in Canada by engaging them with critical resources, partners and opportunities, to drive economic and social benefits for Canada. See www.wavefrontac.com for more details. Wavefront is a registered trademark of Wavefront Wireless Innovation Society of British Columbia.

pressRelease.title: FusionPipe Announces Addition Of Tom Chiu To Its Board Of Advisors
pressRelease.lead:
FusionPipe Software Solutions, a leader in secure BYOD container technology, today announced the addition of Tom Chiu to the company’s board of advisors.

Mr. Chiu brings over 20 years of experience in startups, medium and large corporations, including 15 years of global business development and software licensing in the mobile space. His extensive experience in social/mobile commerce, cloud, SaaS, mobile, consumer electronics, and embedded software is a significant asset to the advisory board of FusionPipe.
pressRelease.body:
FusionPipe Software Solutions, a leader in secure BYOD container technology, today announced the addition of Tom Chiu to the company’s board of advisors.

Mr. Chiu brings over 20 years of experience in startups, medium and large corporations, including 15 years of global business development and software licensing in the mobile space. His extensive experience in social/mobile commerce, cloud, SaaS, mobile, consumer electronics, and embedded software is a significant asset to the advisory board of FusionPipe.

Mr. Chiu has provided mentorship for various startups through SparkLabs and Innospring, and currently acts as a board director for Sand Hill Angels, which was named a top angel group by VentureBeat in 2012. In 2009, Mr. Chiu founded IPforAsia, a broker for a range of high quality technology-related transactions including patents sales and acquisitions, technology transfers, licenses, and strategic alliances. Prior to this, Mr. Chiu held Director roles in Business Development and Sales at NXP Software.

“We are fortunate to be able to welcome Tom to FusionPipe’s board of advisors,” noted Peter Luong, FusionPipe’s founder & CEO, “his remarkable experience with mobile technologies and strong investor network will continue the fast paced growth of FusionPipe as we continue to provide small-medium enterprise the complete, secure, and simplified BYOD solution, ThoriumCloud™."

pressRelease.body:
FusionPipe Software Solutions (“FusionPipe”), a leader in providing world-class, virtually unbreakable and secure mobile data security solutions for Enterprises, today announced the appointment of David Snell as Chief Executive Officer. David will provide leadership in growing and strengthening FusionPipe’s market position as the company prepares to launch its best-inclass mobile security solutions and patent–pending QuikSafe™ Technology.

Also FusionPipe is pleased to report that it has closed an oversubscribed Angel Seed Round that will be used in conjunction with Province of BC and Canadian Government R&D grants to further develop and commercialize QuikSafe™. David has provided mentorship on the FusionPipe Advisory Board since October 2012. Prior to joining FusionPipe, David was Chief Marketing Officer at QuickMobile, and also held senior roles at DEES Communications/NICE Technologies and technology leaders such as IBM, Oracle and Data General (EMC).

“We are fortunate to be able to welcome David to lead FusionPipe’s executive team,” noted Peter Luong, FusionPipe’s founder & Chief Technology Officer, “his remarkable experience with mobile technologies and strong investor network will ensure that we can continue FusionPipe’s fast paced growth. pressRelease.title: FusionPipe Software Solutions Announces Oversubscription of Angel Seed Round and Jim Barney as Angel Director
pressRelease.lead:
FusionPipe Software Solutions (“FusionPipe”), a leader in providing world-class, virtually unbreakable and secure mobile data security solutions for Enterprises, today announced the appointment of Jim Barney as a Director of the Company following a very successful Angel Seed Round.

With an extensive and diverse background as a business executive, Jim has managed both International and Domestic operations in a variety of industry sectors. Having worked 25 years with General Cable, a Fortune 1000 company, in various capacities and locations, he was responsible for the P&L of multiple divisions and was the global M&A executive.
pressRelease.body:
FusionPipe Software Solutions (“FusionPipe”), a leader in providing world-class, virtually unbreakable and secure mobile data security solutions for Enterprises, today announced the appointment of Jim Barney as a Director of the Company following a very successful Angel Seed Round.

With an extensive and diverse background as a business executive, Jim has managed both International and Domestic operations in a variety of industry sectors. Having worked 25 years with General Cable, a Fortune 1000 company, in various capacities and locations, he was responsible for the P&L of multiple divisions and was the global M&A executive.

Jim was nominated to the FusionPipe Board of Directors as an Angel representative following the oversubscribed Angel Seed Round that was recently completed. “We are extremely pleased to have Jim join us on the Board of Directors” noted David Snell, FusionPipe’s Chief Executive Officer, “his extensive background in worldwide operational and executive roles within the telecomm industry and his contacts will be a tremendous asset to FusionPipe as we expand our team and develop our go to market initiatives”.

Said Jim Barney: “FusionPipe has developed a proprietary technology that solves a serious security issue with the mobile transfer of sensitive digital information. Numerous industry sectors, especially healthcare, are in desperate need of a solution and the work done by FusionPipe is simply outstanding. The collaboration between FusionPipe and UBC, SFU and industry leading mobile security partners provides me with confidence that FusionPipe has developed a product that will soon become the standard for others to reach. I am pleased to be part of the board of directors team that will provide advice and guidance to an outstanding organization led by David Snell and Peter Luong. I am excited to be able to provide insight from 30 years as an operational global senior executive with M&A experience”.

This award acknowledges an early-stage technology company that demonstrates significant potential, creativity, and promise for the future. 
“We are very proud to have been chosen as one of the nominees for this prestigious and hi-profile technology award. The BC Technology Impact Awards is a yearly event organized by the BC Technology Industry Organization, with hundreds of local hi-tech companies applying. Some of the criteria the contending companies in the “Most Promising Startup Category” are being judged on are; Value Proposition, Competitive Differentiator, Market Opportunity & Impact on the BC Economy. The winners of the awards in the various categories will be announced at the 21st Annual Technology Impact Awards celebration, which takes place at the Vancouver Convention Center on June 5th 2014. For more information on the 2014 Technology Impact Awards, visit the BCTIA Website at: www.thetias.com.

pressRelease.body:
FusionPipe Software Solutions Inc. (“FusionPipe”), a Vancouver-based leader in providing world-class, password-less and virtually unbreakable and secure mobile data security solutions for Prosumers and Enterprises, today announced the upcoming availability of QuikSafe™ KeyVault™ for iOS and Android and QuikSafe™ HE Container, enabling users to wirelessly and securely access and encrypt their confidential documents residing on their Tablets, without the hassle of having to enter usernames and passwords. Using a FusionPipe Secure Communications Framework over Bluetooth® Smart, encryption keys are physically decoupled and moved to a 2nd Factor (smartphone today and wearables in the near future) for increased security and improved mobile user experience.

“We specifically built QuikSafe™ KeyVault™ & HE Container Apps to answer to the growing demand of ‘Prosumers’ and Enterprises to simplify the process of securing and separating highly sensitive, confidential business documents from their personal data”, says Peter Luong, CTO at FusionPipe Software. “Our unique, patent-pending technology combines a secure Container with defense-grade data protection and password-less authentication capabilities that improves not only overall mobile data security but also adds to the convenience of accessing and controlling encrypted documents anytime, anywhere without the need for time-wasting passwords and usernames”.

QuikSafe™ KeyVault™ for iOS and Android and QuikSafe™ HE Container, are mobile security solutions driven by years of customer feedback, FusionPipe R&D and market demand. The products are part of FusionPipe’s commitment to deliver cutting edge data security and authentication technology using a variety of mobile form factors for convenient authentication, strong unbreakable security, and usage while on the go.

David Snell, CEO at FusionPipe says: “We are ready to show the ‘Prosumer’ user community how strong hyper-encryption and advanced security does not have to compromise ease-of-use. Our smart solutions are both intuitive and scalable and are designed to improve the productivity & ROI of an increasingly mobile workforce”.

QuikSafe™ KeyVault™ for iOS and Android and QuikSafe™ HE Container, apps will be available for free on the iTunes App Store and Google Play by August 31st. QuikSafe™ HE Container (iPad only at this point) will be available on iTunes in the same time frame.

  • Eliminates the need for usernames & passwords
  • Physical decoupling of encryption keys for added security
  • Offers a Secure Document Container for iPads
  • Keeps confidential or Enterprise data separate from personal data
  • ECDH Message Encryption for defense-grade data security
  • Seamless integration with popular Microsoft Office Productivity Suites

pressRelease.title: How I did it: David Snell
pressRelease.subtitle: CEO helped software startup’s founder turn a good idea into a promising product
pressRelease.lead: Business in Vancouver's “How I did it” feature asks business leaders to explain in their own words how they achieved a business goal in the face of significant entrepreneurial challenges. In this week's issue, David Snell talks about how Vancouver startup FusionPipe is getting a toehold in the competitive mobile security market.
pressRelease.body:
FusionPipe CEO David Snell

 

Article Published in Business Vancouver, Tuesday September 9, 2014

Business in Vancouver's “How I did it” feature asks business leaders to explain in their own words how they achieved a business goal in the face of significant entrepreneurial challenges. In this week's issue, David Snell talks about how Vancouver startup FusionPipe is getting a toehold in the competitive mobile security market.

“Peter Luong founded the company in 2010. He had a vision for mobile security and password-less authentication then, and he spent the next four years using his own money, about $500,000, and government grants. And then really he got to the point where he had to make a decision: ‘Do I abandon this, because I've put enough money in?

“When Steve Jobs told us in 2007 what we wanted, which is smartphones, and then in 2010 announced and started delivering the iPad, we really started the march to replace laptops and PCs. Peter knew enough about technology – he was at CIBC Security for some years in Toronto, as well as Nortel and he saw that bring-your-own-device was going to become more common; BlackBerry was very secure but was unfortunately being replaced by consumer Android and iOS devices; passwords were becoming very complex; and security breaches, he knew, were going to start happening in mobile because mobile was just not as mature as the Internet.”

“He started to look at how you could build a separate container, for work-related data, that would be separate from personal and that would encrypt data and also look at a way that a mobile workforce could authenticate themselves without having to use passwords and do that in a secure manner.”

“In September 2013, he was getting ready to look at launching the products in 2014. He was getting married on a beach in Hawaii, saying, ‘OK, what do I do now? I put a lot of money in and my wife's kind of questioning my sanity. Do I get a job, or do I follow my dream?'

“So he followed his dream. He persevered and went out looking for a CEO, which is when he found me. I've been advising Peter since October 2012. What he wanted to do was find a CEO to grow the company, hire staff and bring in the first seed round of the company.”

“We've now gone from an oversubscribed seed round to a late seed round that's already full, and we're in due diligence proceedings for Series A financing in 2015.”

“One of the things Peter was very smart about – and not all entrepreneurs are smart about doing this – he hired law firm Gowling Lafleur Henderson LLP, and did a very, very complex patent. It cost a lot of money for a startup, but we've just got an opinion letter from the Canadian Intellectual Property Office saying that 85% of our patent is unique and patentable, and it’s useful technology. That builds a whole bunch of things for the future. It protects your intellectual property from other folks coming in and gives a lot of credibility to the intellectual property itself when you're talking to investors.”

“We have just been approved for the Apple Store for both our products. We could never have gotten there if we hadn't gotten a team on board to strategize and execute on this plan.”

 

Q&A

Q: What government funding sources were you able to access in the early days of the company?

A: NSERC (Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council of Canada) and Mitacs were the first ones. We have been able to get SRED (Scientific Research and Experimental Development) funds every year. This year was the first time we got an IRAP (Industrial Research Assistance Program) grant.

Q: What is your biggest challenge right now?

A: We are in a very tight talent market here in Vancouver. The best candidates have a choice where they want to work.

pressRelease.title: FusionPipe Software sponsors University of British Columbia (UBC) ECE Capstone Project to develop Gesture Controlled Wearable Solution
pressRelease.lead: FusionPipe Software Solutions Inc. (“FusionPipe”), a Vancouver-based leader in providing world-class, password-less and virtually unbreakable and secure mobile data security solutions for Enterprises, today announced that it is the industry sponsor for a Capstone project with students in UBC’s Electrical Engineering and Computer Engineering (ECE) department to develop a gesture and motion controlled solution primarily for Healthcare environments.
pressRelease.body:
FusionPipe Software Solutions Inc. (“FusionPipe”), a Vancouver-based leader in providing world-class, password-less and virtually unbreakable and secure mobile data security solutions for Enterprises, today announced that it is the industry sponsor for a Capstone project with students in UBC’s Electrical Engineering and Computer Engineering (ECE) department to develop a gesture and motion controlled solution primarily for Healthcare environments.

Capstone is utilizing a Thalmic Labs’ Myo armband, a gesture controlled wearable that uses subtle arm and hand gestures to allow users to operate in a hands-free environment for Healthcare. The project is focused on complementing FusionPipe’s password-less authentication technology utilizing Bluetooth® Smart, wirelessly opening or accessing a PC, computer terminal or mobile device when in proximity, without having to touch a screen or a traditional keyboard and mouse. The Myo armband lets you use the electrical activity produced in a person’s muscles to wirelessly control any device.

Myo armbands use a built-in accelerometer and gyroscope to monitor arm movements and transmits those gestural events to companion apps written on Windows, Mac, iOS or Android.

“This is a perfect opportunity for us to work with some of the smartest engineering students from UBC”, says Peter Luong, FusionPipe’s CTO and Founder. Our goal is to develop a sophisticated solution that could help Healthcare organizations improve productivity, cleanliness and convenience where sterility is imperative.”

The gesture controlled armband will integrate with FusionPipe’s QuikSafe™ technology for password-less authentication over Bluetooth® Low Energy (BLE) which will negate the need for remote controllers, touch pads or secondary devices as well as the need for Healthcare professionals to remove gloves when accessing medical data. Staff will be more productive and will therefore be able to dedicate more time to the important stuff – like patient care.

Says David Snell, CEO of FusionPipe: ”We want to focus on solutions that have the potential to make a significant difference in peoples’ daily lives. Also, having UBC as one of our major strategic academic partners is paramount to the success of our research and development of innovative and cutting edge technologies. We are confident that the Capstone Design Project will be a huge success.”

pressRelease.body:
FusionPipe Software Solutions Inc. (“FusionPipe”), a Vancouver-based leader in providing world-class, password-less, multi factor authentication and data security solutions for Prosumers and Enterprises, today announced it will be launching its first Prosumer version of QuikID™ for iOS and Android, a multi factor user authenticator that allows users to unlock, access, and lock Windows based PC’s and laptops without the need for username, passwords, or additional hardware.

QuikID™ was specifically developed to improve digital identity security and user experience by simplifying the authentication process for Prosumers and Enterprise users. Where most login systems require the use of dongles, smartcards, tokens or OTP’s, or complex identification processes using passwords and usernames, QuikID™ automatically establishes a connection between the user’s smartphone and computer, and wirelessly authenticates the user in a totally secure manner.

“Given the computerized, digital world we live in, and the accompanying need for secure authentication, the amount of time we spend logging in, accessing and/or logging out of computers, laptops and other devices is constantly increasing and is becoming a significant burden on people’s daily lives – not to mention the hard and soft costs associated with password-based security breaches”, says David Snell, CEO and Chairman of FusionPipe. “The two choices we have had in the past are both ineffectual: simple and easy to remember, username and password combinations are easy to use but just as easy to crack; or, complex, long, and hard to remember login credentials that are more secure but make the whole authentication process extremely cumbersome and time-consuming. We decided to use our patent pending QuikSafe™ technology to develop very easy to use, timesaving applications that combine secure convenience with increased productivity without compromising identity security. I think we have found the winning combination in QuikID™”.

QuikID™ mobile apps work in tandem with a FusionPipe Microsoft Windows© app that is easily downloaded from our web site and paired with the users’ smartphone. Once paired for life, the users’ PC or Laptop automatically unlocks when required without the need for usernames or passwords.


Product Features & Benefits - QuikID™ Free Edition

  • Wireless Multi-factor Authentication over secure WiFi
  • Eliminates the need for usernames & passwords
  • Use with biometrics fingerprint touch ID sensor for more convenient authentication
  • Works with both iOS and Android Smartphones
  • Windows Client Software provided for download

 

Figure 1: QuikID™ Free Edition for iPhone users

 

For more information on QuikID™ for iOS, Android and Microsoft Windows, visit: www.fusionpipe.com/solutions

pressRelease.body:
FusionPipe Software Solutions Inc. FusionPipe’s QuikSafe™ technology and QuikID™ applications offer advanced password-less multi factor authentication eliminating the need for complex passwords and offering secure convenience combined with the highest level of data security and identity protection. KeyVault™ and HE™ Container apps provide the same authentication technologies along with hyper-encryption of sensitive documents on Tablets to provide maximum security as well as ease of use.

pressRelease.title: FusionPipe Announces Password-less Smartwatch Authenticator App
pressRelease.lead: FusionPipe Software Solutions Inc. (“FusionPipe”), a Vancouver-based leader in providing world-class, password-less and virtually unbreakable and secure data security and authentication solutions for Prosumers and Enterprises, today announced the November 2014 availability of the world’s first smartwatch authenticator app for Windows.
pressRelease.body:
FusionPipe Software Solutions Inc. (“FusionPipe”), a Vancouver-based leader in providing world-class, password-less and virtually unbreakable and secure data security and authentication solutions for Prosumers and Enterprises, today announced the November 2014 availability of the world’s first smartwatch authenticator app for Windows.

David Snell FusionPipe’s CEO and Chairman made this ‘breakthrough’ product announcement during the 36th Angel Forum in Vancouver in front of more than 50 Angel investors. “Being first to market with our secure smartwatch password-less  authentication app gives us a huge advantage over anyone that’s thinking of solving the password dilemma using either smartwatches or smartphones. Our QuikIDTM product family is the result of years of R&D effort in conjunction with our University partners such as UBC and SFU right here in Vancouver, and with the help of Government grants such as NRC IRAP, MITACS and NSERC. The usefulness and quality of our first Smartwatch application for Android Wear OS is outstanding and we are looking forward to introducing this technology on Apple Watch in the very near future”. 

QuikIDTM offers a unique password-less authentication solution for Prosumers and Enterprises that are looking to simplify the sign-in process for Windows-based PC’s providing the combination of ease of use with higher security. QuikIDTM for Android Wear OS Smartwatches will be in the Google Play App Store by the end of November.

FusionPipe’s QuikID™ applications for iOS and Android smartphones, and now Google Wear OS Smartwatches, offer advanced password-less authentication using these devices over Wi-Fi (QuikID™ Basic) or Bluetooth® Smart (QuikID™ Pro) eliminating the need for entering complex passwords and offering secure convenience combined with the highest level of data security and identity protection.
